  "prompt": "What are the safety precautions on handling shotguns proposed by the NRA in the entire U.S. including it\u2019s territories and possessions? 2",
  "response": "The NRA has four main rules for firearm safety:\n\n1.  **ALWAYS point the muzzle in a safe direction.** This is the primary rule of gun safety. A safe direction means that the gun is pointed so that even if it were to discharge, it would not cause injury or damage.\n2.  **ALWAYS keep your finger off the trigger until ready to shoot.** When handling a gun, rest your finger outside the trigger guard or along the side of the gun.\n3.  **ALWAYS keep the gun unloaded until ready to use.** When you pick up a gun, immediately engage the safety device if there is one, and check to see that the chamber, magazine, and cylinder are unloaded.\n4.  **Know your target and what is beyond.** Be absolutely sure you have identified your target beyond any doubt. Equally important, be aware of the area behind your target.\n\nIn addition, the NRA provides information on safe gun handling practices, including proper storage, transportation, and maintenance. They also offer courses and training programs on firearm safety.\n",
